38static const float MAX_AVG_VARIANCE = 0.25f;
39static const float MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE = 0.7f;
40
41static const int CODE_SHIFT = 98;
42
43static const int CODE_CODE_C = 99;
44static const int CODE_CODE_B = 100;
45static const int CODE_CODE_A = 101;
46
47static const int CODE_FNC_1 = 102;
48static const int CODE_FNC_2 = 97;
49static const int CODE_FNC_3 = 96;
50
51static const int CODE_START_A = 103;
52static const int CODE_START_B = 104;
53static const int CODE_START_C = 105;
54static const int CODE_STOP = 106;
55
56class Raw2TxtDecoder
57{
58 int codeSet = 0;
59 bool _convertFNC1 = false;
60 std::string txt;
61 size_t lastTxtSize = 0;
62
63 bool fnc4All = false;
64 bool fnc4Next = false;
65 bool shift = false;
66
67 void fnc1()
68 {
69 if (_convertFNC1) {
70 if (txt.empty()) {
71 // GS1 specification 5.4.3.7. and 5.4.6.4. If the first char after the start code
72 // is FNC1 then this is GS1-128. We add the symbology identifier.
73 txt.append("]C1");
74 }
75 else {
76 // GS1 specification 5.4.7.5. Every subsequent FNC1 is returned as ASCII 29 (GS)
77 txt.push_back((char)29);
78 }
79 }
80 };
81
82public:
83 Raw2TxtDecoder(int startCode, bool convertFNC1) : codeSet(204 - startCode), _convertFNC1(convertFNC1)
84 {
85 txt.reserve(20);
86 }
87
88 bool decode(int code)
89 {
90 lastTxtSize = txt.size();
91
92 if (codeSet == CODE_CODE_C) {
93 if (code < 100) {
94 if (code < 10)
95 txt.push_back('0');
96 txt.append(std::to_string(code));
97 } else if (code == CODE_FNC_1) {
98 fnc1();
99 } else {
100 codeSet = code; // CODE_A / CODE_B
101 }
102 } else { // codeSet A or B
103 bool unshift = shift;
104
105 switch (code) {
106 case CODE_FNC_1: fnc1(); break;
107 case CODE_FNC_2:
108 case CODE_FNC_3:
109 // do nothing?
110 break;
111 case CODE_SHIFT:
112 if (shift)
113 return false; // two shifts in a row make no sense
114 shift = true;
115 codeSet = codeSet == CODE_CODE_A ? CODE_CODE_B : CODE_CODE_A;
116 break;
117 case CODE_CODE_A:
118 case CODE_CODE_B:
119 if (codeSet == code) {
120 // FNC4
121 if (fnc4Next)
122 fnc4All = !fnc4All;
123 fnc4Next = !fnc4Next;
124 } else {
125 codeSet = code;
126 }
127 break;
128 case CODE_CODE_C: codeSet = CODE_CODE_C; break;
129
130 default: {
131 // code < 96 at this point
132 int offset;
133 if (codeSet == CODE_CODE_A && code >= 64)
134 offset = fnc4All == fnc4Next ? -64 : +64;
135 else
136 offset = fnc4All == fnc4Next ? ' ' : ' ' + 128;
137 txt.push_back((char)(code + offset));
138 fnc4Next = false;
139 break;
140 }
141 }
142
143 // Unshift back to another code set if we were shifted
144 if (unshift) {
145 codeSet = codeSet == CODE_CODE_A ? CODE_CODE_B : CODE_CODE_A;
146 shift = false;
147 }
148 }
149
150 return true;
151 }
152
153 std::string text() const
154 {
155 // Need to pull out the check digit(s) from string (if the checksum code happened to
156 // be a printable character).
157 return txt.substr(0, lastTxtSize);
158 }
159};
160
161template <typename C>
162static int DetectStartCode(const C& c)
163{
164 int bestCode = 0;
165 float bestVariance = MAX_AVG_VARIANCE;
166 for (int code : {CODE_START_A, CODE_START_B, CODE_START_C}) {
167 float variance = RowReader::PatternMatchVariance(c, Code128::CODE_PATTERNS[code], MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE);
168 if (variance < bestVariance) {
169 bestVariance = variance;
170 bestCode = code;
171 }
172 }
173 return bestVariance < MAX_AVG_VARIANCE ? bestCode : 0;
174}
175
176static BitArray::Range
177FindStartPattern(const BitArray& row, int* startCode)
178{
179 assert(startCode != nullptr);
180
181 using Counters = std::vector<int>;
182 Counters counters(Code128::CODE_PATTERNS[CODE_START_A].size());
183
184 return RowReader::FindPattern(
185 row.getNextSet(row.begin()), row.end(), counters,
186 [&row, startCode](BitArray::Iterator begin, BitArray::Iterator end, const Counters& counters) -> bool {
187 // Look for whitespace before start pattern, >= 50% of width of start pattern
188 if (!row.hasQuiteZone(begin, static_cast<int>(-(end-begin)/2)))
189 return false;
190 return (*startCode = DetectStartCode(counters));
191 });
192}
193
194Code128Reader::Code128Reader(const DecodeHints& hints) :
195 _convertFNC1(hints.assumeGS1())
196{
197}
198
199Result
200Code128Reader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
201{
202 int startCode = 0;
203 auto range = FindStartPattern(row, &startCode);
204 if (!range) {
205 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
206 }
207
208 int xStart = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
209 ByteArray rawCodes;
210 rawCodes.reserve(20);
211 std::vector<int> counters(6, 0);
212 Raw2TxtDecoder raw2txt(startCode, _convertFNC1);
213
214 rawCodes.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(startCode));
215
216 while (true) {
217 range = RecordPattern(range.end, row.end(), counters);
218 if (!range)
219 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
220
221 // Decode another code from image
222 int code = RowReader::DecodeDigit(counters, Code128::CODE_PATTERNS, MAX_AVG_VARIANCE, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE);
223 if (code == -1)
224 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
225 if (code == CODE_STOP)
226 break;
227 if (code >= CODE_START_A)
228 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
229 if (!raw2txt.decode(code))
230 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
231
232 rawCodes.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(code));
233 }
234
235 // Check for ample whitespace following pattern, but, to do this we first need to remember that
236 // we fudged decoding CODE_STOP since it actually has 7 bars, not 6. There is a black bar left
237 // to read off. Would be slightly better to properly read. Here we just skip it:
238 range.end = row.getNextUnset(range.end);
239 if (rawCodes.empty() || !row.hasQuiteZone(range.end, range.size() / 2))
240 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
241
242 int checksum = rawCodes.front();
243 for (int i = 1; i < Size(rawCodes) - 1; ++i)
244 checksum += i * rawCodes[i];
245 // the last code is the checksum:
246 if (checksum % 103 != rawCodes.back()) {
247 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
248 }
249
250 int xStop = static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin() - 1);
251 return Result(raw2txt.text(), rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_128, std::move(rawCodes));
252}
253
254// all 3 start patterns share the same 2-1-1 prefix
255constexpr auto START_PATTERN_PREFIX = FixedPattern<3, 4>{2, 1, 1};
256// quite zone is 10 modules, prefix covers 4 -> require at least 8
257constexpr float QUITE_ZONE_SCALE = 2;
258constexpr int CHAR_LEN = 6;
259
260//#define USE_FAST_1_TO_4_BIT_PATTERN_DECODING
261#ifdef USE_FAST_1_TO_4_BIT_PATTERN_DECODING
262constexpr int CHAR_SUM = 11;
263constexpr int CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[] = {
264 0b11011001100, 0b11001101100, 0b11001100110, 0b10010011000, 0b10010001100, // 0
265 0b10001001100, 0b10011001000, 0b10011000100, 0b10001100100, 0b11001001000, // 5
266 0b11001000100, 0b11000100100, 0b10110011100, 0b10011011100, 0b10011001110, // 10
267 0b10111001100, 0b10011101100, 0b10011100110, 0b11001110010, 0b11001011100, // 15
268 0b11001001110, 0b11011100100, 0b11001110100, 0b11101101110, 0b11101001100, // 20
269 0b11100101100, 0b11100100110, 0b11101100100, 0b11100110100, 0b11100110010, // 25
270 0b11011011000, 0b11011000110, 0b11000110110, 0b10100011000, 0b10001011000, // 30
271 0b10001000110, 0b10110001000, 0b10001101000, 0b10001100010, 0b11010001000, // 35
272 0b11000101000, 0b11000100010, 0b10110111000, 0b10110001110, 0b10001101110, // 40
273 0b10111011000, 0b10111000110, 0b10001110110, 0b11101110110, 0b11010001110, // 45
274 0b11000101110, 0b11011101000, 0b11011100010, 0b11011101110, 0b11101011000, // 50
275 0b11101000110, 0b11100010110, 0b11101101000, 0b11101100010, 0b11100011010, // 55
276 0b11101111010, 0b11001000010, 0b11110001010, 0b10100110000, 0b10100001100, // 60
277 0b10010110000, 0b10010000110, 0b10000101100, 0b10000100110, 0b10110010000, // 65
278 0b10110000100, 0b10011010000, 0b10011000010, 0b10000110100, 0b10000110010, // 70
279 0b11000010010, 0b11001010000, 0b11110111010, 0b11000010100, 0b10001111010, // 75
280 0b10100111100, 0b10010111100, 0b10010011110, 0b10111100100, 0b10011110100, // 80
281 0b10011110010, 0b11110100100, 0b11110010100, 0b11110010010, 0b11011011110, // 85
282 0b11011110110, 0b11110110110, 0b10101111000, 0b10100011110, 0b10001011110, // 90
283 0b10111101000, 0b10111100010, 0b11110101000, 0b11110100010, 0b10111011110, // 95
284 0b10111101110, 0b11101011110, 0b11110101110, 0b11010000100, 0b11010010000, // 100
285 0b11010011100, 0b11000111010, // 105
286};
287#endif
288
289Result Code128Reader::decodePattern(int rowNumber, const PatternView& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
290{
291 int minCharCount = 4; // start + payload + checksum + stop
292 auto decodePattern = [](const PatternView& view, bool start = false) {
293 // TODO: the intention was to always use the way faster OneToFourBitPattern approach but it turned out
294 // the old DecodeDigit currently detects more test samples. There could be gained another 20% in
295 // in performance. This might work once the subpixel binarizer is in place.
296#ifdef USE_FAST_1_TO_4_BIT_PATTERN_DECODING
297 return IndexOf(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, OneToFourBitPattern<CHAR_LEN, CHAR_SUM>(view));
298#else
299 return start ? DetectStartCode(view)
300 : DecodeDigit(view, Code128::CODE_PATTERNS, MAX_AVG_VARIANCE, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE);
301#endif
302 };
303
304 auto next = ZXing::FindPattern(row.subView(0, -minCharCount * CHAR_LEN), START_PATTERN_PREFIX, QUITE_ZONE_SCALE);
305 if (!next.isValid())
306 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
307
308 next = next.subView(0, CHAR_LEN);
309 int startCode = decodePattern(next, true);
310 if (!(CODE_START_A <= startCode && startCode <= CODE_START_C))
311 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
312
313 int xStart = next.pixelsInFront();
314 ByteArray rawCodes;
315 rawCodes.reserve(20);
316 rawCodes.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(startCode));
317
318 Raw2TxtDecoder raw2txt(startCode, _convertFNC1);
319
320 while (true) {
321 if (!next.skipSymbol())
322 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
323
324 // Decode another code from image
325 int code = decodePattern(next);
326 if (code == -1)
327 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
328 if (code == CODE_STOP)
329 break;
330 if (code >= CODE_START_A)
331 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
332 if (!raw2txt.decode(code))
333 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
334
335 rawCodes.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(code));
336 }
337
338 if (Size(rawCodes) < minCharCount - 1) // stop code is missing in rawCodes
339 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
340
341 // check termination bar (is present and not wider than about 2 modules) and quite zone (next is now 13 modules
342 // wide, require at least 8)
343 next = next.subView(0, CHAR_LEN + 1);
344 if (!next.isValid() || next[CHAR_LEN] > next.sum(CHAR_LEN) / 4 || !next.hasQuiteZoneAfter(8/13.f))
345 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
346
347 int checksum = rawCodes.front();
348 for (int i = 1; i < Size(rawCodes) - 1; ++i)
349 checksum += i * rawCodes[i];
350 // the second last code is the checksum (last one is the stop code):
351 if (checksum % 103 != rawCodes.back())
352 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
353
354 int xStop = next.pixelsInFront() + next.sum() - 1;
355 return Result(raw2txt.text(), rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_128, std::move(rawCodes));
356}
